      <uri>https://community.sap.com/t5/user/viewprofilepage/user-id/12573</uri>
    </author>
    <content>&lt;P&gt;Hello,&lt;/P&gt;&lt;P&gt;I've a question - is there a possibility (or when will be) to make some of the fields in table in Form/Approval editable and some read-only?&lt;/P&gt;&lt;P&gt;Currently there is a very little configuration possible in table:&lt;/P&gt;&lt;P&gt;&lt;span class="lia-inline-image-display-wrapper lia-image-align-inline" image-alt="nex_0-1721222939865.png" style="width: 700px;"&gt;&lt;img src="https://community.sap.com/t5/image/serverpage/image-id/137746iA9DB0453955EE965/image-dimensions/700x355?v=v2" width="700" height="355" role="button" title="nex_0-1721222939865.png" alt="nex_0-1721222939865.png" /&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/P&gt;&lt;P&gt;We can make only full table 'Read-only' or not.&lt;/P&gt;&lt;P&gt;If we select specific field of table, e.g: 'Nr dziennika', we cannot make it 'editable' (there is no such option):&lt;/P&gt;&lt;P&gt;&lt;span class="lia-inline-image-display-wrapper lia-image-align-inline" image-alt="nex_1-1721223093015.png" style="width: 400px;"&gt;&lt;img src="https://community.sap.com/t5/image/serverpage/image-id/137749i349130D501C62051/image-size/medium?v=v2&amp;amp;px=400" role="button" title="nex_1-1721223093015.png" alt="nex_1-1721223093015.png" /&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/P&gt;&lt;P&gt;We've a case, that we want to make some kind of 'checkbox' in Form/Approval, in which user can decide which 'incoming correspondance' he wants to 'Approve' and which he wants to 'Reject'. It seems to be unfortunately not possible currently with this technology.&lt;/P&gt;&lt;P&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/P&gt;&lt;P&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/P&gt;&lt;P&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/P&gt;</content>
    <link href="https://community.sap.com/t5/technology-q-a/sap-build-process-automation-editable-field-in-table-in-form-approval/qaq-p/13763506"/>
    <published>2024-07-17T15:34:22.735000+02:00</published>
